This PR attempts to set up initial binary packages for `@swc/cli`. PR **intentionally** does not contain most of actual implementations yet. Actual implementation will come later once after we get agreement on the migration paths.

1. `@swc/core` v2 

- `swc_cli` will be built as native binary, supports a single subcommand `compile` which current `@swc/cli` supports.
- `@swc/core`'s platform specific optional deps will includes binary to swc_cli for each platform
- `@swc/cli` provides interop to subcommand-less invocation
```
// pseudo 
// `@swc/cli/index.ts

if (args[0] != 'compile') {
  console.warn(`deprecated: v3 will require to invoke cli with subcommand only');
  exec('swc_cli_bin', 'compile', ...args);
}
else {
 exec('swc_cli_bin', ...args);
}
```

2. `@swc/core` v3
- retiring, let `@swc/cli` mark as deprecated 
- `@swc/core` specifics `bin` property in package.json to point native binary directly or have wrapper shell script to do those. Either cases, node.js should not be required to invoke binaries
- all of cli development consolidated into main repo

**Pros**
- full rust binary
- aligned development in single repo
- 0 v8 warmup time: invoking cli becomes very effective, similar to esbuild's cli performs.

**Cons**
- binary size: this effectively increases pkg size as we need to ship additional binary
- compilation time: may increase time to create binary & node bindings


**Related issue (if exists):**
- relates with #1589

