This PR seeks to integrates the excellent [Neural-API](https://github.com/joaopauloschuler/neural-api) by Joao Paulo Schwarz Schuler as a TMusafaBitmap's `ClassifyBitmap` new method.
    
It includes a model trained on 60,000 images over 100 different classes (CIFAR-100) but other models can be trained using Neural-API.

Rather than a finished integration, this PR is a question: is this something you would be interested in adding into Simba? (I love the idea of a multiplatform desktop scripting environment and it might be possible to extended into a full RPA open source solution.)

If this goes in line with the direction of the project, then there is the question of whether to integrate this into Simba or package it as an extension. (Integrating the CIFAR classifier adds extra 3.2Mb to Simba.)

If we want to integrate this into Simba proper, the current code has a number of issues I'd need your help and guidance:

* The neural network model is kept in disk. It would be nice to compile it as a resource and load it directly from the executable.
* The neural network model is loaded every time the method is called. I tried setting it up as  a global variable but that did not work (most probably because each script executes in a separate environment).
* `TMusafaBitmap.ResizeBilinear` produces inferior results to `TBitmap.StretchDraw` and that impacts the predictions significantly (the classifier works on 32x32 images).
* The result of the model are not stable (I don't know whether that's a problem in neural-api or an incompatibility with the execution environments, it'll take a deeper debugging to find out).

Here is a little Simba script showcasing the behaviour of the new method:

```pascal
program classifyexample;
var
  m: TMufasaBitmap;
  labels: TStringArray;
  scores: TSingleArray;
  bestMatch: String;
  i: Integer;
begin
  for i := 1 to 10 do
  begin
    m := TMufasaBitmap.CreateFromFile('/path/to/some/image/with/a/pear');
    m.ClassifyBitmap(labels,scores,bestMatch);
    WriteLn(bestMatch);
    m.Free;
end;
end.
```

To see all the scores:

```pascal
program classifyexample;
var
  m: TMufasaBitmap;
  labels: TStringArray;
  scores: TSingleArray;
  bestMatch: String;
  i: Integer;
begin
  m := TMufasaBitmap.CreateFromFile('/path/to/some/image');
  m.ClassifyBitmap(labels,scores,bestMatch);
  for i := Low(scores) to High(scores) do
     WriteLn(i, ' ', labels[i], ': ', scores[i]);
  WriteLn(bestMatch);
  m.Free;
end.
```

